Description: DGI is an independent “full service” investor relations and corporate communications firm started in 1991.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: DGI is an independent “full service” investor relations and corporate communications firm started in 1991. From its Wall Street area offices, DGI provides experienced strategic counsel to a select number of clients aimed at increasing their visibility, bringing them face to face with investors, and successfully managing their financial communications to achieve fair long term market value. The firm’s principal focus in recent years has been on U.S. investor and public relations for a growing number of foreign and domestic small and micro-cap companies, including several in the “ about to go public” stage. Working with smaller companies, they are able to use their extensive “big cap” experience to establish a credible IR and PR function and couple this with a well honed talent for scoping out and building upon what makes each client uniquely attractive. As needed, they bring into each situation a wide network of reliable contacts and associates to assist in such areas as boosting trading volume, adding market makers, developing research coverage, obtaining financing, as well as bringing companies public. They also have an outstanding track record in media placement, both electronic and print. Prior to founding DGI, Ken Donenfeld served as executive vice president of D.F. King, advising a variety of companies as well as such dissident shareholders as Carl Icahn and Harold Simmons on investor relations, corporate communications and media relations. Previously, after beginning his career at Georgeson & Co., he became executive vice president of Robert Marston and Associates, a leading independent public relations firm. At Marston he directed financial media and investor relations programs for several “emerging growth” companies as well as such industry leaders as Anheuser- Busch, Wang, and International Multifoods. Donenfeld became a recognized leader, too, in creating IR and corporate communications programs for European companies whose shares are traded in the U.S., introducing to U.S. investors such companies as Novo Industries, Pharmacia AB, Gambro, ADT, And London International Group. At DGI, Donenfeld added a heavy concentration in the Dutch market, building U.S. awareness of such leading companies as KBB, Randstad, and Vopak. The firm also gained recognition for pioneering work on behalf of emerging Eastern European companies. Other clients have included: Pentair (manufacturing); Grow (chemicals); Equity Oil (energy); Uni-Invest (reits); Eiger Technology (electronics); Coda Octopus (marine technology/ security); Gevity HR (human resources management) which ranked among the leading gainers on NASDAQ in 2007; and CyberDefender (Internet Security).

Uses any device that connects to the Web and has a keyboard. We have our own private “cloud;” there is nothing to download or to install. Student registers, and is on his way. Teacher uses another program to assemble exams from our database in very short time. Students use paper and pencil or, with the help of yet another program, take those exams cheat-proof over the Internet.     With our College Tutor, we offer color, still-, and moving media in 2-D and 3-D, sound, homework projects, exams, and self-assessment. In addition, we have the entire infrastructure available to serve students and teachers alike that could turn our system into an online school.    Great care was taken and no expenses spared to make the system convenient, fast, and cheat- and hacker proof. For example, during exam time students may sit next to each other with their laptops but still would have great difficulties to copy from one another.    Exam scores are relayed back to the student for feedback, and to the teacher and a designated regional/state assessment center for evaluation. Education policy makers will have instant information in their hands that up to now they can only wish for.

From baby heartbeats to wedding vows, our customers are constantly wowing us with their imaginations.   The future of Soundwave Art™ is looking bright, with many ideas on the horizon. Keep checking our website to stay up to date on our fun and ever-evolving endeavor. Description: Let's Go Ref connects sports officials with event organizers to automate payments.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: LetsGoRef operates in the financial services sector. The company offers a platform that connects referees and sports officials with sports events that require their services. It provides a streamlined process for event organizers to find and hire the right officials for their events. The platform also offers features for officials to manage their schedules, accept assignments, and receive payments. It aims to simplify the process of hiring sports officials and improve the efficiency of sports event organization.
